WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.320 --> 00:00:06.200
Today we're excited to release a brand new

00:00:06.200 --> 00:00:09.160
ChatGPT on web, desktop and mobile.

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:11.400
Now ChatGPT goes from just answering

00:00:11.400 --> 00:00:13.720
questions to doing work for you

00:00:13.720 --> 00:00:15.900
by connecting to all of your tools.

00:00:16.240 --> 00:00:18.100
I can switch from chat to work

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:20.360
and this interface
should feel very familiar.

00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:22.900
But instead of just having conversations,

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.960
I can hand off real work from here.

00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:27.380
Take a look at my calendar, Slack

00:00:27.380 --> 00:00:30.140
and Drive and help me prepare for my day.

00:00:30.420 --> 00:00:32.520
While that's running,
let me show you plugins.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.120
Some of them connect to the apps you use,

00:00:35.300 --> 00:00:38.000
others bundle role-specific
workflows for sales,

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:39.960
data science, marketing and more.

00:00:39.980 --> 00:00:41.180
And here we go.

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:43.620
It found everything
about my day, the notes

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:45.460
and how to prepare for my next meetings.

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:48.000
The next thing I want
is for this to happen

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:49.540
without me asking every time.

00:00:50.860 --> 00:00:52.060
Let's try this.

00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:54.040
Can you be my Chief of Staff

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:56.260
and give me a briefing every morning

00:00:56.260 --> 00:00:58.380
of what I have to prepare for the day?

00:00:58.660 --> 00:01:00.700
And while the World Cup is going on,

00:01:00.860 --> 00:01:03.100
can you actually give me the scores

00:01:03.100 --> 00:01:04.800
of the German team and any other

00:01:04.800 --> 00:01:06.000
matches that I care about?

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:07.200
And that's it.

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:08.980
The automation is set and I don't

00:01:08.980 --> 00:01:10.900
have to remember to ask again tomorrow.

00:01:11.140 --> 00:01:13.200
And by the way, this also works on the go.

00:01:13.420 --> 00:01:15.240
The same chat is already on my phone.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:17.720
I can start on the web, leave

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:19.560
my desk and keep going on my mobile.

00:01:20.100 --> 00:01:22.040
Now when I want ChatGPT to work

00:01:22.040 --> 00:01:23.660
with my local files and projects,

00:01:23.820 --> 00:01:25.080
I move to the desktop app.

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:27.220
On the left, I can see all

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:29.280
of my projects and everything ChatGPT

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:31.020
is working on, but this time

00:01:31.020 --> 00:01:32.640
with all of my local files as well.

00:01:33.140 --> 00:01:34.920
For me, this is a big shift.

00:01:35.160 --> 00:01:36.740
I can give it the context,

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:38.940
hand off the work, and then come back

00:01:38.940 --> 00:01:40.600
when it needs me or has something ready.

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:42.640
Let's look at something more involved.

00:01:42.900 --> 00:01:44.960
I'm going to show you three different

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:48.120
examples across marketing,
data analytics and engineering.

00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:50.500
Let's say I'm building a fictional

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:52.460
neobank called Hudson and we're

00:01:52.460 --> 00:01:54.360
getting ready to launch our mobile app.

00:01:54.660 --> 00:01:55.860
Here's the launch site.

00:01:56.040 --> 00:01:58.040
All of these visuals were generated

00:01:58.040 --> 00:02:00.440
using ChatGPT and image generation.

00:02:00.760 --> 00:02:02.580
All I did was give it my logo,

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:05.820
my brand guidelines,
and it's incredible how

00:02:05.820 --> 00:02:07.820
many different directions I can explore

00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:10.200
and how consistent they
are with our brand.

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:12.340
The next thing I want to do is translate

00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:13.540
this into an ad campaign.

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.180
We can now create

00:02:15.180 --> 00:02:17.380
mood boards for what this could look like.

00:02:17.380 --> 00:02:19.740
I can now imagine many ideas in less time

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:21.540
than it would take for me to explore one.

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:23.700
I love this takeover concept.

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:25.200
It looks amazing.

00:02:25.280 --> 00:02:27.040
Next, I asked ChatGPT to turn

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:28.920
these into a deck to share with my team.

00:02:29.820 --> 00:02:32.080
Beautiful. Ready for our
launch review meeting today.

00:02:36.900 --> 00:02:38.500
Let's say we just launched the app.

00:02:38.640 --> 00:02:40.400
Switching gears to data science, I want

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:41.960
to understand how it's actually going.

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:45.020
The metrics, the user
feedback, team conversations,

00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:47.600
launch plans, all are in different places.

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:50.180
And I use ChatGPT to bring
them all together.

00:02:50.800 --> 00:02:53.480
Since it's a data question,
ChatGPT automatically

00:02:53.480 --> 00:02:55.960
brought in the right skills and workflows.

00:02:56.420 --> 00:02:57.800
And this is what it came up with.

00:02:58.080 --> 00:03:01.180
Activation rates, signups,
and even this onboarding funnel.

00:03:01.640 --> 00:03:03.320
Here I'm using my own data store,

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:04.960
but your data could just as easily

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:06.880
live in spreadsheets or a data warehouse.

00:03:07.380 --> 00:03:08.940
The launch looks healthy overall,

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:10.620
but something looks off in Mexico.

00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:13.880
In fact, ChatGPT already flagged it and it

00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:15.960
thinks it might be a
phone onboarding issue.

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:17.960
So we'll have a look at this in a moment.

00:03:18.180 --> 00:03:20.260
I could build this into a deck and share

00:03:20.260 --> 00:03:22.000
this with my team, but a real-life

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:23.720
dashboard would be much more useful.

00:03:24.040 --> 00:03:26.720
So I asked it to pull these
metrics into this dashboard.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:28.780
I can visualize it

00:03:28.780 --> 00:03:31.440
in the in-app browser
and I can click to annotate.

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:34.720
Add a one-line summary
on how the launch is going.

00:03:35.060 --> 00:03:37.220
I love collaborating with ChatGPT like

00:03:37.220 --> 00:03:39.180
this and seeing the changes happen live.

00:03:39.800 --> 00:03:41.460
Awesome. It looks good.

00:03:42.040 --> 00:03:43.800
Now I want to share it with my team.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.320
Sites is a great way to do this.

00:03:45.720 --> 00:03:48.660
It lets me publish websites
directly from ChatGPT.

00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:51.140
Publish this dashboard, share the link

00:03:51.140 --> 00:03:53.200
in my team channel, and make sure

00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:55.000
that the metrics are updated every day.

00:03:55.400 --> 00:03:56.600
And just like that,

00:03:56.640 --> 00:03:58.460
we have built and shared the dashboard.

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:00.300
Next, it's time to switch

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:02.160
to Codex and put my engineering hat

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:04.280
on to fix this mobile app issue.

00:04:04.460 --> 00:04:05.940
If you're already a Codex user,

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:08.020
it's the same Codex you know and love.

00:04:08.260 --> 00:04:09.700
Now inside of ChatGPT.

00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:12.520
Thanks to ChatGPT, we know where to look,

00:04:12.640 --> 00:04:15.520
but let's confirm what the customer
is actually experiencing.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:17.480
I'm going to use the Simulator

00:04:17.480 --> 00:04:18.980
and bring the app on the screen

00:04:18.980 --> 00:04:22.120
and take an appshot by pressing Cmd-Cmd.

00:04:22.840 --> 00:04:24.800
Review the phone onboarding in Mexico,

00:04:25.060 --> 00:04:26.520
then in Germany to compare

00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:28.680
and click around the main screens.

00:04:28.940 --> 00:04:31.600
You can think of an appshot
as a smarter screenshot.

00:04:31.900 --> 00:04:33.600
It gives it the app I'm looking at

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:35.920
and the context it needs
to take action on.

00:04:36.540 --> 00:04:38.860
It's now triggering
background Computer Use.

00:04:39.200 --> 00:04:40.700
That is not my cursor.

00:04:41.020 --> 00:04:43.020
This is ChatGPT using my app.

00:04:43.400 --> 00:04:45.600
When ChatGPT doesn't
have a dedicated plugin,

00:04:45.920 --> 00:04:47.600
it can use your computer directly.

00:04:47.740 --> 00:04:48.940
It can do the same thing

00:04:48.980 --> 00:04:50.900
in the browser with the Chrome extension.

00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:52.560
Copying and pasting data,

00:04:52.760 --> 00:04:55.260
browsing sites, or checking a workflow.

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:57.700
It looks like customers are indeed

00:04:57.700 --> 00:05:00.580
getting stuck when they're entering
a valid Mexican phone number.

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:03.300
That explains why the
activation rates are lower.

00:05:03.400 --> 00:05:04.620
Let's also have it check

00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:07.240
everything works great for other countries
in the background.

00:05:07.460 --> 00:05:08.900
Now for the final step,

00:05:09.060 --> 00:05:10.800
let's actually have it fix the problem.

00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:12.380
Prepare a fix for the

00:05:12.380 --> 00:05:14.380
phone number validation bug in Mexico.

00:05:14.920 --> 00:05:16.740
And when it's ready, I can see

00:05:16.740 --> 00:05:18.560
the diff directly within Codex,

00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:20.920
review the changes, and publish this PR

00:05:20.920 --> 00:05:23.060
so we can ship a new version of the app.

00:05:23.320 --> 00:05:25.360
So this is the new ChatGPT.

00:05:25.620 --> 00:05:28.220
One place where you
can delegate real work.

00:05:28.500 --> 00:05:30.600
Whether that's in your apps, your

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:33.480
local projects, or even your
computer and browser.

00:05:33.800 --> 00:05:35.100
There's really no task

00:05:35.100 --> 00:05:37.080
that ChatGPT cannot help you with.

00:05:37.540 --> 00:05:39.340
Hey Chat, I'm done with my demo.

00:05:39.520 --> 00:05:41.120
Can you play some walkout music?

00:05:42.360 --> 00:05:43.820
This was only a quick tour

00:05:43.820 --> 00:05:46.080
and we can't wait to see
what you do with it.

